<div type="abstract"><head>Rat an Hans und Georg von Streitberg</head><p>Der Rat bittet um Herausgabe von drei aus einem Fass beschlagnahmten Pelzröcken aus Eichhornfell des Albrecht Scheffein, Bürger zu Nürnberg.</p>
</div>
<!--This div could possibly contain the analytic portion of the edition.-->
<div type="linguisticAnalysis"><ab><w join="" lemma="" msd="" part="" pos=""><fLib><f name=" "/></fLib></w></ab></div>
</front>
<body><div type="diplomatic"><pb facs="#facs_240" id="119v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee"><ab facs="#facs_240_r2l14">Hanſen vnd Görgen von Streẏperg </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content"><ab facs="#facs_240_r2l15"><expan>Lieb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> Hans vnd Görg / vns hat fürgelegt <expan>Albr<ex>echt</ex></expan> Scheffein </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_240_r2l16"><expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>burg<ex>er</ex></expan> / vvie daʒ Jr Jm dreẏ vehwemmin kürſen auſʒ </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_240_r2l17"><expan>eine<ex>m</ex></expan> vaſʒ genomen habt / vnd maint daʒ die auſʒlewte ſein </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_240_r2l18">ſein ſolten / Nu hat der <expan>eg<ex>enante</ex></expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex></expan> <expan>b<ex>urger</ex></expan> vor vns cʒu den <expan>heẏlig<ex>en</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_240_r2l19">behabt / daʒ <expan>dieſelb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> ııȷ vehkürſen ſein vnd <expan>and<ex>er</ex>r</expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>r</expan> <expan>burge<ex>r</ex></expan> </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_240_r2l20">ſein / Alſo / daʒ khein auſʒman vveder teil noch gemain daran </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_240_r2l21">hab / <expan>dar<ex>ümb</ex></expan> <expan>Ro<ex>gamus</ex></expan> / daʒ Jr dem <expan>eg<ex>enanten</ex></expan> <expan>vnſ<ex>er</ex>m</expan> <expan>b<ex>urger</ex></expan> <expan>dıeſelb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> ſein </ab>
<ab facs="#facs_240_r2l22">kürſen <expan>wıdergeb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> vvöllet / Als etc das <expan>wölle<ex>n</ex></expan> etc <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> ut <expan>ſup<ex>ra</ex></expan></ab>
</div>
</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_240" id="119v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Hansen und Görgen von Streyperg </ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>Lieb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> Hans und Görg, uns hat fürgelegt
                                <expan>Albr<ex>echt</ex></expan> Scheffein,
                            <expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>burg<ex>er</ex></expan>, wie daz ir im drey vehwemmin kürsen ausz
                                <expan>eine<ex>m</ex></expan> vasz genomen habt und maint, daz die
                        auszlewte sein sein solten. Nu hat der <expan>eg<ex>enante</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex></expan>
<expan>b<ex>urger</ex></expan> vor uns czu den
                            <expan>heylig<ex>en</ex></expan> behabt, daz
                            <expan>dieselb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> iii vehkürsen sein und
                                <expan>and<ex>er</ex>r</expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>r</expan>
<expan>burge<ex>r</ex></expan> sein, also daz khein auszman weder teil noch
                        gemain daran hab. <expan>Dar<ex>umb</ex></expan>
<expan>ro<ex>gamus</ex></expan>, daz ir dem
                            <expan>eg<ex>enanten</ex></expan>
<expan>uns<ex>er</ex>m</expan>
<expan>b<ex>urger</ex></expan>
<expan>dieselb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> sein kürsen
                            <expan>widergeb<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wöllet. Als etc. Das
                                <expan>wölle<ex>n</ex></expan> etc. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan> ut
                                <expan>sup<ex>ra</ex></expan>.</ab>
</div>
</div></body>
